26
00:01:10,000 --> 00:01:14,000
and I will show thee things which must be hereafter.

27
00:01:14,000 --> 00:01:16,000
And immediately I was in the spirit

28
00:01:16,000 --> 00:01:19,000
and behold, a throne was set in heaven

29
00:01:19,000 --> 00:01:21,000
and one sat on the throne.

30
00:01:21,000 --> 00:01:23,000
And he that sat was to look upon

31
00:01:23,000 --> 00:01:25,000
like a jasper and a sardine stone.

32
00:01:25,000 --> 00:01:28,000
And there was a rainbow round about the throne

33
00:01:28,000 --> 00:01:31,000
in sight like unto an emerald.

34
00:01:31,000 --> 00:01:33,000
I've titled the message this evening,

35
00:01:33,000 --> 00:01:35,000
In Heaven, part one.

36
00:01:35,000 --> 00:01:37,000
Why is it part one?

37
00:01:37,000 --> 00:01:39,000
Because it's gonna be two or three parts

38
00:01:39,000 --> 00:01:42,000
before we get through the entirety of this fourth chapter.

39
00:01:42,000 --> 00:01:44,000
But I want you to remember, hold your place here,

40
00:01:44,000 --> 00:01:46,000
just turn a page or two back in your Bibles

41
00:01:46,000 --> 00:01:49,000
and go to the Revelation chapter one in verse number 19

42
00:01:49,000 --> 00:01:51,000
and find as we begin to remind ourselves

43
00:01:51,000 --> 00:01:55,000
now that God has provided in this book of Revelation

44
00:01:55,000 --> 00:01:58,000
an outline for the book of Revelation.

45
00:01:58,000 --> 00:02:01,000
Not every book of the Bible contains an outline

46
00:02:01,000 --> 00:02:04,000
in the beginning of the book, but this one does.

47
00:02:04,000 --> 00:02:06,000
And we find here in Revelation one,

48
00:02:06,000 --> 00:02:08,000
in verse number 19, he says,

49
00:02:08,000 --> 00:02:11,000
write the things which thou hast seen

50
00:02:11,000 --> 00:02:13,000
and the things which are

51
00:02:13,000 --> 00:02:16,000
and the things which shall be hereafter.

52
00:02:16,000 --> 00:02:18,000
And so we find in this verse of Scripture

53
00:02:18,000 --> 00:02:21,000
that God provides the three sections,

54
00:02:21,000 --> 00:02:23,000
if you will, of the book of Revelation

55
00:02:23,000 --> 00:02:25,000
and provides for us an outline

56
00:02:25,000 --> 00:02:27,000
at the very beginning of this book.

57
00:02:27,000 --> 00:02:29,000
And we find that the first section

58
00:02:29,000 --> 00:02:32,000
is the things which thou hast seen.

59
00:02:32,000 --> 00:02:33,000
And that's chapter number one.

60
00:02:33,000 --> 00:02:37,000
Revelation chapter number one is that first section

61
00:02:37,000 --> 00:02:38,000
of the book of Revelation,

62
00:02:38,000 --> 00:02:41,000
the things which thou hast seen.

63
00:02:41,000 --> 00:02:44,000
Then he says, and the things which are.

64
00:02:44,000 --> 00:02:48,000
And we understand that to be Revelation two and three,

65
00:02:48,000 --> 00:02:50,000
the churches that are being addressed,

66
00:02:50,000 --> 00:02:51,000
the seven churches.

67
00:02:51,000 --> 00:02:53,000
We studied through each of those letters

68
00:02:53,000 --> 00:02:56,000
and we understand that these are local churches

69
00:02:56,000 --> 00:02:58,000
that were in existence at the time of the writing.

70
00:02:58,000 --> 00:03:00,000
They were literal churches.

71
00:03:00,000 --> 00:03:02,000
We made it clear that they were not

72
00:03:02,000 --> 00:03:04,000
all the churches that existed.

73
00:03:04,000 --> 00:03:07,000
There were more than seven churches in existence

74
00:03:07,000 --> 00:03:10,000
at the time of the writing of the book of Revelation.

75
00:03:10,000 --> 00:03:11,000
But these are the seven churches

76
00:03:11,000 --> 00:03:14,000
that God chose to send a letter to

77
00:03:14,000 --> 00:03:17,000
and had given that instruction to John.

78
00:03:17,000 --> 00:03:20,000
And we understand that it really is representative,

79
00:03:20,000 --> 00:03:23,000
if you will, chapters two and three of the church age.

80
00:03:23,000 --> 00:03:26,000
And we said this as we studied through chapters two and three,

81
00:03:26,000 --> 00:03:28,000
as you look at the differences with the churches,

82
00:03:28,000 --> 00:03:33,000
that they are not laid out in such a way

83
00:03:33,000 --> 00:03:36,000
that the beginning of the church age

84
00:03:36,000 --> 00:03:39,000
was every church was like the church at Ephesus

85
00:03:39,000 --> 00:03:41,000
and the end of the church age,

86
00:03:41,000 --> 00:03:44,000
that every church has to be like the church of the Laodiceans.

87
00:03:44,000 --> 00:03:48,000
I believe that throughout the entirety of the church age,

88
00:03:48,000 --> 00:03:51,000
and we don't know exactly how long the church age is.

89
00:03:51,000 --> 00:03:53,000
It's been about 2,000 years at this point.

90
00:03:53,000 --> 00:03:56,000
We don't know exactly the length of the church age.

91
00:03:56,000 --> 00:03:59,000
But what we do know is that throughout the history

92
00:03:59,000 --> 00:04:03,000
of the church, that there have been churches

93
00:04:03,000 --> 00:04:06,000
that would be like each of these churches.

94
00:04:06,000 --> 00:04:08,000
You can be a church in 2025

95
00:04:08,000 --> 00:04:10,000
that is like the church of the Laodiceans,

96
00:04:10,000 --> 00:04:13,000
or you could be like the church at Sardis

97
00:04:13,000 --> 00:04:16,000
or Thyatira or Ephesus, et cetera, et cetera.

98
00:04:16,000 --> 00:04:19,000
And so we find that the second section

99
00:04:19,000 --> 00:04:22,000
of the book of Revelation is the things which are,

100
00:04:22,000 --> 00:04:24,000
according to Revelation 119,

101
00:04:24,000 --> 00:04:28,000
and that would be represented for us in Revelation 2 and 3,

102
00:04:28,000 --> 00:04:31,000
dealing with the church age.

103
00:04:31,000 --> 00:04:34,000
The third and final section of the book is,

104
00:04:34,000 --> 00:04:37,000
as it's described in Revelation 1 and verse 19,

105
00:04:37,000 --> 00:04:41,000
and the things which shall be hereafter.

106
00:04:41,000 --> 00:04:43,000
And so we find that in verse number one

107
00:04:43,000 --> 00:04:46,000
of chapter number four, he says after this,

108
00:04:46,000 --> 00:04:48,000
that's the way that the verse begins,

109
00:04:48,000 --> 00:04:51,000
but if you look at the end of the verse, he says,

110
00:04:51,000 --> 00:04:54,000
and I will show thee things, notice,

111
00:04:54,000 --> 00:04:57,000
which must be hereafter.

112
00:04:57,000 --> 00:05:00,000
And so he said in Revelation 1 and 19

113
00:05:00,000 --> 00:05:03,000
that he said to write the things which thou hast seen

114
00:05:03,000 --> 00:05:05,000
and the things which are and the things

115
00:05:05,000 --> 00:05:08,000
which shall be hereafter.

116
00:05:08,000 --> 00:05:12,000
And now the Lord says in chapter four and verse number one,

117
00:05:12,000 --> 00:05:16,000
I will show thee things which must be hereafter.

118
00:05:16,000 --> 00:05:19,000
And so Revelation 4 and verse number one

119
00:05:19,000 --> 00:05:22,000
begins the third section of the book of Revelation

120
00:05:22,000 --> 00:05:24,000
and it ends in chapter 22.

121
00:05:24,000 --> 00:05:26,000
We would say that this third section

122
00:05:26,000 --> 00:05:28,000
of the book of Revelation is roughly divided

123
00:05:28,000 --> 00:05:31,000
into three particular aspects.

124
00:05:31,000 --> 00:05:33,000
The first one is the tribulation,

125
00:05:33,000 --> 00:05:35,000
which is Revelation six through 19.

126
00:05:35,000 --> 00:05:37,000
The second of that is the millennium,

127
00:05:37,000 --> 00:05:38,000
which is Revelation 20.

128
00:05:38,000 --> 00:05:42,000
And then you have eternity in Revelation 21 and 22.

129
00:05:42,000 --> 00:05:43,000
In Revelation four and five,

130
00:05:43,000 --> 00:05:46,000
what you have in this passage of scripture

131
00:05:46,000 --> 00:05:50,000
is really the scene into the throne room of heaven.

132
00:05:50,000 --> 00:05:53,000
In chapters four and five, you have where God

133
00:05:53,000 --> 00:05:57,000
is providing us and providing John,

134
00:05:57,000 --> 00:06:00,000
obviously the one who had the revelation.

135
00:06:00,000 --> 00:06:03,000
He's giving to us an opportunity

136
00:06:03,000 --> 00:06:05,000
to see into the throne room of heaven

137
00:06:05,000 --> 00:06:07,000
and what a scene it is.

138
00:06:07,000 --> 00:06:10,000
You read Revelation four and five, it's exciting.

139
00:06:10,000 --> 00:06:12,000
Make you want to shout and praise the Lord

140
00:06:12,000 --> 00:06:14,000
because our God is so good.

141
00:06:14,000 --> 00:06:16,000
And we find that as we look at this text of scripture,

142
00:06:16,000 --> 00:06:19,000
I've entitled it in heaven.

143
00:06:19,000 --> 00:06:20,000
Why?

144
00:06:20,000 --> 00:06:23,000
Because we find that the voice that he heard,

145
00:06:23,000 --> 00:06:25,000
he says it were of a trumpet talking with me

146
00:06:25,000 --> 00:06:28,000
in verse number one, come up hither.

147
00:06:28,000 --> 00:06:30,000
And we said that in chapter number four

148
00:06:30,000 --> 00:06:34,000
and verse number two, and immediately I was in the spirit

149
00:06:34,000 --> 00:06:38,000
and behold, a throne was set in heaven.

150
00:06:38,000 --> 00:06:43,000
And God allows for John to be transported to heaven.

151
00:06:43,000 --> 00:06:46,000
And so we find that the timing is obvious.

152
00:06:46,000 --> 00:06:48,000
The setting is obvious.

153
00:06:48,000 --> 00:06:50,000
It's in heaven, according to chapter four

154
00:06:50,000 --> 00:06:51,000
and verse number two.

155
00:06:51,000 --> 00:06:52,000
And we talk about heaven,

156
00:06:52,000 --> 00:06:55,000
he's talking about the habitation of God.

157
00:06:55,000 --> 00:06:57,000
We can talk about the heavens,

158
00:06:57,000 --> 00:07:00,000
meaning that which we can see in the skies

159
00:07:00,000 --> 00:07:03,000
and the stars and what have you.

160
00:07:03,000 --> 00:07:05,000
But we find that here in Revelation four,

161
00:07:05,000 --> 00:07:07,000
when he talks about in heaven,

162
00:07:07,000 --> 00:07:09,000
he's not talking about just being in the atmosphere,

163
00:07:09,000 --> 00:07:10,000
being in the universe.

164
00:07:10,000 --> 00:07:13,000
He's talking about the place where God dwells,

165
00:07:13,000 --> 00:07:14,000
the habitation of God.

166
00:07:14,000 --> 00:07:18,000
And so we find that as we look at this text of scripture,

167
00:07:18,000 --> 00:07:19,000
even by way of introduction,

168
00:07:19,000 --> 00:07:22,000
we find and we're reminded of the truth

169
00:07:22,000 --> 00:07:26,000
that heaven is indeed a real place.

170
00:07:26,000 --> 00:07:27,000
You know, there's some people today

171
00:07:27,000 --> 00:07:32,000
that want to try to give this idea that heaven is not real.

172
00:07:32,000 --> 00:07:34,000
It's just a figment of your imagination.

173
00:07:34,000 --> 00:07:36,000
You make heaven whatever you want it to be

174
00:07:36,000 --> 00:07:39,000
and you can have heaven on earth

175
00:07:39,000 --> 00:07:42,000
and you hear that type of thing and so on and so forth.

176
00:07:42,000 --> 00:07:43,000
But I want you to know this evening

177
00:07:43,000 --> 00:07:46,000
that heaven is a real place.

178
00:07:46,000 --> 00:07:49,000
And we find that not only is heaven a real place,

179
00:07:49,000 --> 00:07:50,000
but as we look at the text

180
00:07:50,000 --> 00:07:53,000
